And I'm scared.

276
00:17:14,961 --> 00:17:16,212
I'm really scared.

277
00:17:17,631 --> 00:17:18,632
Shit!

278
00:17:20,800 --> 00:17:22,176
Are you serious?

279
00:17:22,635 --> 00:17:23,720
Are you okay?

280
00:17:24,429 --> 00:17:25,847
Did they force you?

281
00:17:26,765 --> 00:17:29,101
I had to agree
in exchange for my freedom.

282
00:17:29,559 --> 00:17:32,664
The only reason my parents
allowed me to live in a condo

283
00:17:32,688 --> 00:17:35,398
and choose my own course is because.

284
00:17:36,107 --> 00:17:37,733
I agreed to this engagement.

285
00:17:45,366 --> 00:17:46,701
What if

286
00:17:47,076 --> 00:17:48,662
he's ugly?

287
00:17:49,078 --> 00:17:51,414
Shit, that would suck!

288
00:17:52,332 --> 00:17:54,936
Sev, I'm not even thinking
about his looks.

289
00:17:54,960 --> 00:17:58,523
I'm just scared that
he might not be a good person.

290
00:17:58,547 --> 00:18:00,483
What if you get married

291
00:18:00,507 --> 00:18:02,110
and he looks ugly?

292
00:18:02,134 --> 00:18:04,779
And his breath stinks?
And he has a bad attitude?

293
00:18:04,803 --> 00:18:05,905
He might be smart and rich,

294
00:18:05,929 --> 00:18:07,431
but what if he looks disgusting?

295
00:18:08,222 --> 00:18:10,933
Now, I'm starting to think
about those things.

296
00:18:11,518 --> 00:18:14,186
Sev, those weren't even
part of my concerns earlier.

297
00:18:14,896 --> 00:18:15,896
Okay.

298
00:18:16,022 --> 00:18:17,316
How about this?

299
00:18:18,775 --> 00:18:19,984
Meet him first.

300
00:18:20,777 --> 00:18:22,194
See if he's your type.

301
00:18:22,820 --> 00:18:24,047
If not,

302
00:18:24,071 --> 00:18:26,301
tell your family I'm your boyfriend.

303
00:18:26,325 --> 00:18:29,118
If they try to make you marry him,

304
00:18:29,368 --> 00:18:31,078
just say you'll elope with me.

305
00:18:32,663 --> 00:18:34,434
Come on, use me!

306
00:18:34,458 --> 00:18:36,185
You guys always do it anyway.

307
00:18:36,209 --> 00:18:37,501
I'll take care of it!

308
00:18:40,422 --> 00:18:42,441
That's an impossible plan,

309
00:18:42,465 --> 00:18:44,193
but thank you, Sev.

310
00:18:44,217 --> 00:18:45,676
It made me laugh.

311
00:18:48,221 --> 00:18:50,598
But seriously, Sam…

312
00:18:51,391 --> 00:18:53,018
If you need someone to talk to,

313
00:18:53,393 --> 00:18:54,644
I'm here, okay?

314
00:18:55,354 --> 00:18:56,355
Don't be shy.

315
00:18:59,273 --> 00:19:00,459
And if

316
00:19:00,483 --> 00:19:02,837
those guys are really your type…

317
00:19:02,861 --> 00:19:04,904
- Gym bros like me…
- Shit.

318
00:19:05,489 --> 00:19:07,132
Just let me know, I know a lot of guys.

319
00:19:07,156 --> 00:19:08,616
Sevi! Stop it!

320
00:19:08,825 --> 00:19:11,161
Stop! You're so annoying.

321
00:19:15,123 --> 00:19:17,267
Welcome to college life, kids!

322
00:19:17,291 --> 00:19:19,728
Finally, you'll start maturing!

323
00:19:19,752 --> 00:19:20,481
Just like me.

324
00:19:20,505 --> 00:19:22,106
You're so full of yourself, Yanna!

325
00:19:22,130 --> 00:19:23,983
You're only a year older than them,

326
00:19:24,007 --> 00:19:25,776
and you act like you're so mature.

327
00:19:25,800 --> 00:19:27,861
Hey! Well, of course,
I'm studious, you know?

328
00:19:27,885 --> 00:19:29,530
As if! I saw you playing billiards.

329
00:19:29,554 --> 00:19:30,531
Ohhh.

330
00:19:30,555 --> 00:19:32,241
Well, congratulations! You have eyes.

331
00:19:32,265 --> 00:19:34,369
Guys, come on. Wait…

332
00:19:34,393 --> 00:19:37,537
This is Sevirous. He's a scholar.

333
00:19:37,561 --> 00:19:38,915
Show them. Show them.

334
00:19:38,939 --> 00:19:40,707
Yes, man. Let's go!

335
00:19:40,731 --> 00:19:42,752
And he kept being pursued

336
00:19:42,776 --> 00:19:45,879
to join the basketball team,
now that's Sevi!

337
00:19:45,903 --> 00:19:47,005
What now, guys?

338
00:19:47,029 --> 00:19:49,257
I'm going to face off
with your basketball teams.

339
00:19:49,281 --> 00:19:50,842
You all can just cry about it!

340
00:19:50,866 --> 00:19:53,012
- Really, now?
- You all can just cry about it.

341
00:19:53,036 --> 00:19:54,347
Sevi, that's great.

342
00:19:54,371 --> 00:19:55,913
You know what? I'll cheer for you.

343
00:19:57,332 --> 00:19:59,643
Are you serious, Sam?

344
00:19:59,667 --> 00:20:01,562
Now I feel guilty about trash talking.

345
00:20:01,586 --> 00:20:03,773
And my trash talk was on point, too.

346
00:20:03,797 --> 00:20:06,590
Oh. How about you three?
How's architecture?

347
00:20:06,924 --> 00:20:08,384
Easy.

348
00:20:08,676 --> 00:20:12,763
And we'll take it easy until graduation.

349
00:20:13,347 --> 00:20:14,408
Hey! Come on, guys.

350
00:20:14,432 --> 00:20:16,077
We might jinx ourselves
and next thing you know,

351
00:20:16,101 --> 00:20:18,329
we'll be crying over our plates.

352
00:20:18,353 --> 00:20:20,581
No one's going to cry
in this family, okay?

353
00:20:20,605 --> 00:20:23,942
That's just architecture.
You're Via, Kierra, and Luna.

354
00:20:24,567 --> 00:20:26,004
You guys are amazing!

355
00:20:26,028 --> 00:20:27,588
Look at Sevi. He's in engineering,

356
00:20:27,612 --> 00:20:29,465
but all he thinks about is basketball.

357
00:20:29,489 --> 00:20:30,800
Ah, basketball.

358
00:20:30,824 --> 00:20:34,720
Whatever! You scholars of the
people should just keep quiet!

359
00:20:34,744 --> 00:20:35,679
Am I wrong?

360
00:20:35,703 --> 00:20:36,515
OMG!

361
00:20:36,539 --> 00:20:39,308
You guys know how hard it
was to get into his university.

362
00:20:39,332 --> 00:20:41,226
It was so easy for me. I mean…

363
00:20:41,250 --> 00:20:42,061
Right?

364
00:20:42,085 --> 00:20:43,085
So arrogant.

365
00:20:45,380 --> 00:20:47,065
He's blushing again.

366
00:20:47,089 --> 00:20:49,819
- Let's toast!
- Let's just toast, guys!

367
00:20:49,843 --> 00:20:51,279
Let's toast!

368
00:20:51,303 --> 00:20:53,805
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

369
00:21:16,994 --> 00:21:19,599
Tomorrow is Clyden's graduation party.

370
00:21:19,623 --> 00:21:21,500
Don't forget.

371
00:21:45,106 --> 00:21:46,775
Sam, let's go?

372
00:21:53,656 --> 00:21:55,301
Hi, Naomi!

373
00:21:55,325 --> 00:21:56,617
How's your studies?

374
00:21:57,201 --> 00:21:58,537
Why do you even care?

375
00:22:00,454 --> 00:22:02,516
Naomi, she's asking you politely.

376
00:22:02,540 --> 00:22:04,185
Don't be rude!

377
00:22:04,209 --> 00:22:05,961
Answer properly!

378
00:22:06,586 --> 00:22:07,604
Mom, it's okay.

379
00:22:07,628 --> 00:22:08,922
No, it's not okay!

380
00:22:09,213 --> 00:22:12,675
If we tolerate her rudeness,
she'll keep doing it.

381
00:22:15,345 --> 00:22:16,488
Naomi,

382
00:22:16,512 --> 00:22:18,573
are you going to apologize to your sister,

383
00:22:18,597 --> 00:22:20,307
or do I have to ground you again?

384
00:22:20,892 --> 00:22:22,519
Mom, I said it's okay.

385
00:22:23,019 --> 00:22:24,354
S-Sorry.

386
00:22:26,189 --> 00:22:27,982
No, Naomi, it's okay.

387
00:22:28,482 --> 00:22:30,460
Come on, get dressed.
We're going to a party.

388
00:22:30,484 --> 00:22:31,736
Oh no…

389
00:22:31,828 --> 00:22:33,404
She's not coming. It's just us.

390
00:22:34,114 --> 00:22:36,615
Why? Mom, we can't leave her here.

391
00:22:36,768 --> 00:22:38,144
Yes, we can!

392
00:22:38,451 --> 00:22:39,702
What?

393
00:22:40,162 --> 00:22:42,705
You want to show off your dad's
bastard child to everyone?

394
00:22:43,205 --> 00:22:44,207
- Mom!
- Let's go!

395
00:23:06,645 --> 00:23:08,230
Senator Vera is here.

396
00:23:08,522 --> 00:23:09,458
Chris!

397
00:23:09,482 --> 00:23:11,710
- Sam, smile.
- Senator Vera!

398
00:23:11,734 --> 00:23:13,504
Stephen Vera, wow!
Glad you can make it!

399
00:23:13,528 --> 00:23:14,505
You're going to get married to a Ramirez.

400
00:23:14,529 --> 00:23:15,590
And with your lovely wife too.

401
00:23:15,614 --> 00:23:16,424
- Hi!
- Hi!

402
00:23:16,448 --> 00:23:17,216
Hi there!

403
00:23:17,240 --> 00:23:18,177
Hello!

404
00:23:18,201 --> 00:23:19,534
How are you?

405
00:23:19,826 --> 00:23:20,887
We're good.

406
00:23:20,911 --> 00:23:22,388
You know, I wouldn't
miss this for anything.

407
00:23:22,412 --> 00:23:24,139
Congratulations to your son.

408
00:23:24,163 --> 00:23:25,957
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

409
00:23:26,249 --> 00:23:28,585
You know, he's the
only one that I could trust.

410
00:23:29,627 --> 00:23:31,606
Oh, by the way, is this Samantha?

411
00:23:31,630 --> 00:23:32,857
- Yes.
- Is this really her?

412
00:23:32,881 --> 00:23:33,923
Yes!

413
00:23:35,049 --> 00:23:37,570
This is Dr. Christopher Ramirez,

414
00:23:37,594 --> 00:23:38,970
the owner of Ramirez Medical.

415
00:23:38,994 --> 00:23:40,162
Remember, Maui?

416
00:23:40,587 --> 00:23:42,923
And of course, Chris,
this is my daughter,

417
00:23:43,266 --> 00:23:44,952
Samantha Maureen Vera.

418
00:23:44,976 --> 00:23:46,954
Wow, what a beautiful young lady.

419
00:23:46,978 --> 00:23:48,246
Thank you, sir. Hello, sir.

420
00:23:48,270 --> 00:23:49,916
Hello, how are you doing?
Pleased to meet you.

421
00:23:49,940 --> 00:23:51,792
I've heard a lot of good things about you.

422
00:23:51,816 --> 00:23:52,834
Thank you.

423
00:23:52,858 --> 00:23:55,629
Wait, I'll introduce you to my son. Okay?

424
00:23:55,653 --> 00:23:56,654
Wait.

425
00:23:57,071 --> 00:23:58,073
Clyden?

426
00:23:58,656 --> 00:23:59,657
Clyden?

427
00:24:13,003 --> 00:24:17,092
Oh, shit. He's exactly my type.

428
00:24:29,229 --> 00:24:30,271
Get over here.

429
00:24:35,234 --> 00:24:38,464
Clyden, you've met
the great Senator Vera.

430
00:24:38,488 --> 00:24:39,506
- Senator.
- Hello.

431
00:24:39,530 --> 00:24:42,089
- And his lovely wife.
- Hi! Hi, Clyden.

432
00:24:42,461 --> 00:24:45,131
And his lovely daughter, Samantha.

433
00:24:45,744 --> 00:24:46,913
Nice to meet you.

434
00:24:50,364 --> 00:24:51,792
Nice to meet you as well.

435
00:24:55,797 --> 00:24:57,048
Get to know each other.

436
00:24:57,464 --> 00:24:58,465
Mingle.

437
00:24:58,758 --> 00:24:59,776
Okay?

438
00:24:59,800 --> 00:25:02,386
Come on, let's leave them
so they can talk.

439
00:25:02,460 --> 00:25:03,460
Okay.

440
00:25:11,424 --> 00:25:12,800
What the fuck?

441
00:25:13,122 --> 00:25:16,459
Why is he looking at me
like that? Is he judging me?

442
00:25:16,483 --> 00:25:18,193
Samantha, right?

443
00:25:20,279 --> 00:25:21,280
Yes.

444
00:25:21,614 --> 00:25:22,882
How shall I call you?

445
00:25:22,906 --> 00:25:24,260
I don't know.

446
00:25:24,284 --> 00:25:25,593
Babe?

447
00:25:25,617 --> 00:25:27,787
Since we're getting married, right?

448
00:25:30,832 --> 00:25:33,534
Physical appearance? Exactly my type.

449
00:25:34,001 --> 00:25:35,471
Attitude?

450
00:25:35,496 --> 00:25:36,788
Hell no.

451
00:25:43,840 --> 00:25:45,843
What the hell is that guy's deal?

452
00:25:45,867 --> 00:25:47,827
Why is he so fucking rude?

453
00:25:48,141 --> 00:25:51,087
Is he acting that way because
he's just as frustrated as I am?

454
00:25:52,125 --> 00:25:54,287
For sure he also got forced into this.

455
00:25:54,672 --> 00:25:57,364
If that's the case, then I can't blame him.

456
00:26:08,577 --> 00:26:09,662
Sam!

457
00:26:11,288 --> 00:26:12,414
Can we talk?

458
00:26:13,921 --> 00:26:15,990
Is he going to apologize?

459
00:26:18,337 --> 00:26:19,713
Yes, sure.

460
00:26:21,340 --> 00:26:23,259
You're the child of a corrupt politician.

461
00:26:23,718 --> 00:26:26,887
I've attended numerous
protests against your dad.

462
00:26:27,430 --> 00:26:28,597
He's the worst.

463
00:26:30,099 --> 00:26:32,394
He has no business
being in public service.

464
00:26:32,644 --> 00:26:34,287
We're just not going to get along.

465
00:26:34,311 --> 00:26:35,311
Well,

466
00:26:35,814 --> 00:26:37,327
I don't like you either.

467
00:26:37,690 --> 00:26:40,652
You're an asshole
who is so full of himself.

468
00:26:40,984 --> 00:26:42,463
Just because you graduated cum laude

469
00:26:42,487 --> 00:26:44,989
doesn't mean you can
look down on everyone else.

470
00:26:45,230 --> 00:26:46,990
How can you say that about me?

471
00:26:47,325 --> 00:26:48,802
Do you even know me?

472
00:26:48,826 --> 00:26:50,869
Well, you're judging me
based on my parents.

473
00:26:51,538 --> 00:26:52,806
You don't know me either.

474
00:26:52,830 --> 00:26:54,790
I don't need to know you.

475
00:26:54,931 --> 00:26:56,207
I know people like you.

476
00:26:57,210 --> 00:26:58,377
My god!

477
00:26:59,378 --> 00:27:01,297
You really are something, huh?

478
00:27:02,632 --> 00:27:04,169
We can't marry each other.

479
00:27:04,384 --> 00:27:05,384
I agree.

480
00:27:06,260 --> 00:27:07,421
Why did you even accept this?

481
00:27:10,306 --> 00:27:11,958
I made a deal, okay?

482
00:27:12,182 --> 00:27:14,059
My college program, condo unit,

483
00:27:14,145 --> 00:27:15,730
car, and a lot more.

484
00:27:16,019 --> 00:27:18,147
Why are you blaming me?
You accepted this, too.

485
00:27:18,288 --> 00:27:19,913
I can't disappoint my dad.

486
00:27:20,525 --> 00:27:22,402
I'm the best son among the three.

487
00:27:23,944 --> 00:27:25,171
Lame.

488
00:27:25,195 --> 00:27:26,196
Wow,

489
00:27:26,655 --> 00:27:30,093
coming from someone who
asked for superficial things?

490
00:27:30,578 --> 00:27:32,193
Superficial things?

491
00:27:32,618 --> 00:27:34,648
That's the only freedom
I'm holding on to.

492
00:27:37,355 --> 00:27:38,607
You don't know my struggles.

493
00:27:38,633 --> 00:27:40,092
And you know mine?

494
00:27:41,413 --> 00:27:43,180
I'm never judge mental of people,

495
00:27:43,204 --> 00:27:45,082
but I'm treating him this way.

496
00:27:45,299 --> 00:27:48,760
Maybe I'm just projecting
my frustrations onto him.

497
00:27:53,516 --> 00:27:55,727
- Hey, I'm sorry—
- You know what?

498
00:27:56,269 --> 00:27:58,371
Let's just act like we're on good terms

499
00:27:58,395 --> 00:28:00,856
and that we're falling in love
in front of our parents.

500
00:28:01,065 --> 00:28:02,793
We have to fool them

501
00:28:02,817 --> 00:28:06,278
that we have a deep connection
until someone makes a mistake

502
00:28:06,338 --> 00:28:08,048
and then we end the engagement.

503
00:28:08,655 --> 00:28:09,907
Let's say…

504
00:28:11,409 --> 00:28:12,463
You cheated on me.

505
00:28:12,872 --> 00:28:13,832
Me?

506
00:28:13,865 --> 00:28:14,824
Why me?

507
00:28:14,871 --> 00:28:16,086
I could never cheat.

508
00:28:16,455 --> 00:28:17,600
And it can't be me.

509
00:28:17,624 --> 00:28:18,708
It's your idea.

510
00:28:19,000 --> 00:28:19,500
Whatever.

511
00:28:19,750 --> 00:28:21,752
Let's just think about it
when the time comes.

512
00:28:22,191 --> 00:28:23,192
Right now,

513
00:28:23,554 --> 00:28:24,971
the more we resist,

514
00:28:25,125 --> 00:28:27,251
the more they'll push the engagement.

515
00:28:27,907 --> 00:28:30,702
So, we have to act like
we really like each other.

516
00:28:33,890 --> 00:28:34,973
Okay?

517
00:28:36,518 --> 00:28:37,519
Fine.

518
00:28:38,519 --> 00:28:39,854
Let's go back inside.

519
00:28:40,664 --> 00:28:41,664
What?

520
00:28:42,201 --> 00:28:43,287
What are you doing?

521
00:28:43,311 --> 00:28:44,311
Yuck.

522
00:28:44,483 --> 00:28:46,611
Of course, you need to hold my hand.

523
00:28:52,157 --> 00:28:53,492
Are you nervous?

524
00:28:53,663 --> 00:28:55,010
Why is your hand wet?

525
00:28:55,036 --> 00:28:56,036
Yuck.

526
00:28:57,832 --> 00:29:00,883
Seems like things are
going well between you two.

527
00:29:02,544 --> 00:29:03,961
All that's missing is a ring.

528
00:29:04,836 --> 00:29:06,798
You don't have to
worry about that, Stephen.

529
00:29:07,839 --> 00:29:08,816
Cy,

530
00:29:08,840 --> 00:29:12,773
go to your room because I have
something for you and Sam.

531
00:29:13,096 --> 00:29:14,096
Sure, Dad.

532
00:29:14,638 --> 00:29:15,638
Let's go.

533
00:29:16,723 --> 00:29:17,723
Go!

534
00:29:48,047 --> 00:29:49,298
They're engagement rings.

535
00:29:50,508 --> 00:29:51,509
So corny.

536
00:29:51,968 --> 00:29:52,969
Why are there two rings?

537
00:29:53,972 --> 00:29:55,307
You're wearing one, too?

538
00:29:55,332 --> 00:29:56,375
Apparently.

539
00:29:59,492 --> 00:30:01,703
So, the whole world knows I'm engaged.

540
00:30:02,510 --> 00:30:04,512
Let's just wear it and remove it after.

541
00:30:04,538 --> 00:30:05,538
Give me.

542
00:30:06,901 --> 00:30:07,901
Let me.

543
00:30:17,117 --> 00:30:18,117
What?

544
00:30:19,690 --> 00:30:22,192
Give me your hand.

545
00:30:46,564 --> 00:30:47,773
Don't get all giddy.

546
00:30:50,652 --> 00:30:51,693
Feeling...

547
00:30:53,278 --> 00:30:54,446
Now put mine on.

548
00:30:55,239 --> 00:30:56,699
Can't you wear it yourself?

549
00:30:57,532 --> 00:30:58,534
Come on.

550
00:30:59,743 --> 00:31:00,743
Fine.

551
00:31:12,923 --> 00:31:14,299
There. We're done.

